{"word":"ἐξήκω","slug":"ἐξήκω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐξήκω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ξω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to have reached</i> a certain point, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>of Time, <i>to have run out</i> or <i>expired, to be over</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of prophecies, dreams, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a> <i>to turn out true</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}